    <body>
        <p>Converts the cursor to Arrow mode, which lets you create a curvy arrow shape. After you select this button, you can click anywhere in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> to identify the starting point for the arrow. When you move the cursor, a straight line shows where the arrow will be placed. When you release the cursor, an arrow is created. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Arrow_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="" MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Arrow Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Object_Properties_Window_Pane.htm#ArrowObjectProperties" MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Arrow Shape Properties</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
    </body>
